places.perex: A tiny nature park most known as a habitat for water birds. Perfect for nature lovers and a great place for a walk.

places.name: Tahiti Beach
places.perex: A gorgeous beach. The soft sand here and the shallow water are perfect for smaller kids.

places.name: Pinder's Point Lighthouse
places.perex: This beautiful lighthouse has a long history of navigating beyond it. Recently restored and reactivated.

places.name: Dead Man's Reef
places.perex: This pleasantly-named reef is home to many species of marine life and makes for a great snorkelling and diving spot.

places.name: The Healing Hole
places.perex: You need a private boat to get there, but this sulphur spring can apparently cure various illnesses.

places.name: Rainbow Reef
places.perex: A popular snorkelling spot. Swim around and see the marine life that lives around the reef.

places.name: Gold Rock Beach
places.perex: The national park hides a true gem of a beach. Calm, clean and beautiful - one of the best on the islands.

places.name: Parliament Square Cultural Center
places.perex: Do not miss this hidden gem. A spectacular tour on Bahamian culture done by the locals themselves.

places.name: Bay Street
places.perex: The main street of the island - you can find most of its attractions here, including a jail housed in a cave and more.

places.name: Hartford Cave
places.perex: The Arawak natives used to live in this cave - many artefacts and cave wall paintings were found here.

places.name: Ben Bay Beach
places.perex: A picture-perfect beach. Sheltered by the bay, so the water is very calm here.

places.name: Great Cut
places.perex: True to its name, this dramatic underwater wall is one of the hidden diving spots of the Bahamas.

places.name: Current Cut
places.perex: The super-fast current separates the two island and is a popular diving spot for the experienced.

places.name: North & South Marine Parks
places.perex: The third longest barrier reef in the world is protected by these two parks. A diver's heaven - do not miss if diving is your thing!

places.name: Cape Santa Maria Beach
places.perex: This remote, vast, sandy beach is a treat for anyone who's ever dreamed of a secluded island vacation. A gem of a beach.

places.name: Columbus Monument, Beach & Lighthouse
places.perex: The place where Columbus first landed on the continent is adorned by a monument and a lighthouse.

places.name: Dannenberg Beach
places.perex: This great beaches is a perfect spot for bathing and tanning. There are also trees that provide some shade if the sun gets too hot.

places.name: Tilloo Cay
places.perex: One of the islands around here that invite you to just lay down and relax. Beautiful nature and picture-perfect beaches.

places.name: Fortune Hill Plantation
places.perex: Ruins of an 18th century plantation with quite an atmosphere. A little distant, but nonetheless a rewarding trip.

places.name: Dixon Hill Lighthouse
places.perex: This 19th century lighthouse surprisingly still works and is operated manually. A fascinating sight.

places.name: North Beaches
places.perex: The most remote island in the Bahamas is lined by divine yet deserted beaches. Great for both swimming and snorkelling.

places.name: Tuna Alley
places.perex: A picturesque diving spot lined by walls of coral. The tuna often swim through here, but there are also sharks and other marine life.

places.name: Twin Cove Beach
places.perex: Two beaches connect into one here. Great for swimming, snorkelling and other water activities.

places.name: The Lone Tree
places.perex: A curious scenery. The tree was washed up here during a hurricane and has become the island's landmark ever since.

places.name: Turtle Sound
places.perex: This pristine body of water is one of the Bahamas' natural wonders. Wander through the mangroves and see the birds and marine life here.

places.name: Elizabeth Harbour
places.perex: This nice harbour is completely natural and a favourite amongst the owners of many ships. An intriguing sight.

places.name: Devil’s Backbone
places.perex: Actually a reef that was given its malicious name for the shipwrecks it caused. A great diving destination.

places.name: Ten Bay Beach & Cave
places.perex: A picture-perfect beach which looks quite different at low and high tide. The cave here is inhabited by bats.

places.name: Sandy Point Estate
places.perex: Ruins of an 18th century plantation house and other facilities. Feel free to explore since they are well-preserved.

places.name: Abaco National Park
places.perex: This protected land is the home of over 100 species of birds, including the rare Bahamian parrot. A must for nature lovers.

places.name: Pelican Cays Land & Sea Park
places.perex: This nature park is probably most thrilling underwater where you can find marine life and extensive underwater caves.

places.name: Curtis Creek & North Beach
places.perex: A quiet spot where you can meet the birds and turtles or just enjoy the peaceful sea and snorkelling opportunities.

places.name: Hoffman's Cay Blue Hole
places.perex: This blue hole is more than 180 meters deep and a home to a colony of oysters. One of the fun diving sites on the islands.

places.name: Love Hill Beach
places.perex: This long beach stretches on and on, making this beach nearly deserted. Great for snorkelling and fishing.

places.name: Manjack Cay
places.perex: A gorgeous island not inhabited by many. Great for swimming, snorkelling and exploring its hidden corners.

places.name: Alice Town Beach
places.perex: This vast stretch of sand is one of the many amazing beaches  on these islands. A peaceful place where you can enjoy the sun.

places.name: Compass Cay
places.perex: A beautiful secluded island. There are almost no facilities, but that's balanced with the stunning nature and marine life.

places.name: Drain Bay Beach
places.perex: This secluded beach and its extraordinary beauty are worth the visit if you're nearby. Green grass, white sand and blue sea.

places.name: Sandy Point Beach
places.perex: This quaint settlement is lined with a long, sandy beach. A great spot for fishing and dolphin-watching.

places.name: Gaulding's Cay
places.perex: A beautiful remote beach where you won't meet anyone else. Great for children and for snorkelling-lovers.

places.name: Club Amnesia
places.perex: One of the best local clubs. Every night is a themed night here with its own unique atmosphere.

places.name: Abraham's Bay
places.perex: The heavenly bay is beautiful both above and under the surface. A wonderful snorkelling spot.

places.name: Surfer's Beach
places.perex: The name says it all. Said to be one of Bahamas' best beaches for surfing - a must if you're into the sport.

places.name: Big Bay Beach
places.perex: A peaceful beach which is a pleasure to visit. Take a walk and pick up some seashells or just swim around in the warm sea.

places.name: Old Bight Beach
places.perex: Bahamas' typical idyllic beach. Pinkish sands, gentle breeze and the calming sea are its main perks.

places.name: Small Hope Bay Beach
places.perex: A marvellous beach right next to a lodge. A relaxing place perfect for all water activities.

places.name: Cappuccino's Italian Restaurant
places.perex: A pleasant restaurant serving Italian cuisine with their own home-made pasta. The premises are tiny, so book in advance.
